cebbootStatusByte.description: This object indicates the status of the last boot. Bit 2 = Bank 0/1 Active (0 = Bank 0, 1 = Bank 1), Bit 1 = Bank 1 Fail and Bit 0 = Bank 0 Fail (0 = Pass, 1 = Fail)

cebbank2CRC.name: cebbank2CRC

cebflashBankARev.name: cebflashBankARev

cebflashBankBRev.name: cebflashBankBRev

trapCEBConfigChangeInteger.name: trapCEBConfigChangeInteger
trapCEBConfigChangeInteger.description: This trap is issued if configuration of a single variable with integer type was changed (via ANY interface). TrapChangedValueInteger variable may contain current reading of that variable. trapPerceivedSeverity - 'indeterminate'

trapCEBConfigChangeDisplayString.name: trapCEBConfigChangeDisplayString
trapCEBConfigChangeDisplayString.description: This trap is issued if configuration of a single variable with DispalayString type was changed (via ANY interface). TrapChangedValueDisplayString variable may contain current reading of that variable. trapPerceivedSeverity - 'indeterminate'

trapCEBfanCurrentAlarm.name: trapCEBfanCurrentAlarm
trapCEBfanCurrentAlarm.description: This trap is issued when the Fan Current parameter goes out of range. trapAdditionalInfoInteger variable contains current reading of the this parameter.

trapCEBModuleTempAlarm.name: trapCEBModuleTempAlarm
trapCEBModuleTempAlarm.description: This trap is issued when the Module Temperature parameter goes out of range. trapAdditionalInfoInteger variable contains current reading of the this parameter.

trapCEBFlashAlarm.name: trapCEBFlashAlarm
trapCEBFlashAlarm.description: This trap is issued when the Laser Modules detects an error during Flash memory operations.

trapCEBBankBootAlarm.name: trapCEBBankBootAlarm
trapCEBBankBootAlarm.description: This trap is issued when the Laser Modules detects an error while booting from bank 0 or bank 1.

trapCEBAlarmDataCRCAlarm.name: trapCEBAlarmDataCRCAlarm
trapCEBAlarmDataCRCAlarm.description: This trap is issued when the Alarm Data CRC is incorrect.

trapCEBFactoryDataCRCAlarm.name: trapCEBFactoryDataCRCAlarm
trapCEBFactoryDataCRCAlarm.description: This trap is issued when the Factory Data CRC is incorrect.
